p/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 14.45633, "shard": "04", "shelf_id": "sn86076356, 1908-04-27, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/nvln", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["united states", "winnemucca", "humboldt", "nevada"], "subject_headings": ["United States--Nevada--Humboldt--Winnemucca"], "subjects": [{"humboldt": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:humboldt&fo=json"}, {"nevada": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:nevada&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"winnemucca": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:winnemucca&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-06-30T19:26:16.229Z", "title": "The Silver state news (Winnemucca, Nev.), April 27, 1908", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/1908-04-27/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn86076356", "https://search.catalog.loc.gov/instances/9a3f0748-83ba-5c12-b52c-8fd6d92f6a30"], "batch": ["nvln_deeth_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1907", "description": ["Semiweekly Vol. 1, no. 1 (June 20, 1907)-v. 3, no. 43 (Sept. 7, 1909). Frequent misnumberings. Silver state (Winnemucca, Nev. : 1909) (DLC)sn 86076247 (OCoLC)13789007"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:24:59.140Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "catalog-split-10", "catalog", "ndnp/newspapers", "main-catalog-split-10", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/", "image_url": [], "index": 2, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [40.9723383, -117.7279389], "location": ["united states", "winnemucca", "humboldt", "nevada"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-117.7279389, 40.9723383], "number": ["original", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2025-07-01t13:41:03", "sn86076247", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/1907-06-20/ed-1/", "2020-07-27t09:41:06.116128", "1", "228", "sn86076224", "2766-4937", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/1909-09-07/ed-1/", "online resource", "eureka library", "microfilm service copy", "sn86076356", "14066969"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["chronicling america", "the silver state news (winnemucca, nev.) 1907-1909", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division", "catalog"], "publication_frequency": ["semiweekly"], "score": 50.070923, "shelf_id": "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn86076356", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "catalog", "usnd"], "subject": ["united states", "winnemucca", "humboldt", "winnemucca (nev.)", "nevada", "newspapers"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:20:06.081Z", "title": "The Silver state news.", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn86076356/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2021270604/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["kelley, e. d."], "date": "1870", "dates": ["[1870 TO 1903]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.), Oct. 7, 1874-Apr. 29, 1903 Began March 22, 1870; ceased with vol. 40, no. 56 (Apr. 29, 1903). Title from publisher's statement: Winneumcca republican, Nov. 17, 1902-Apr. 29, 1903; Daily silver state, Oct. 7, 1874-Jan. 28, 1880. Published at Winnemucca, Sept. 10, 1874-Apr. 29, 1903. Publishers: John I. Ginn, 1870-1871; John Booth, 1871; R.L. Tilden, 1871-1872; J.J. Hill & Co., 1872-<1876>. Editor: E.D. Kelley, 1874-<1876>. Vol. V, No. 135 (February 15 1875); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 11, 2020). Vol. XL, No. 156 (April 29, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 11, 2020). Daily silver state 2766-4929 (DLC) 2021270605 (OCoLC)1230242976"], "digitized": true, "extract_